HEADWORD: Elytrum
<hw>El"y*trum</hw>
<pr>(-tr<?/m)</pr></mhw> <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Elytra</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<grk>'e`lytron</grk>, fr. <grk>'ely`ein</grk> to roll round.]</ety>
<fld>(Zo⟦oum⟧l.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>One of the anterior pair of
wings in the Coleoptera and some other insects, when they are thick and
serve only as a protection for the posterior pair.</def> See
<er>Coleoptera</er>. <sd>(b)</sd> <def>One of the shieldlike dorsal
scales of certain annelids. See <er>Ch⟦ae⟧topoda</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

